'''Malamalama''' pe '''poto''' o se masani, faʻalauiloaina, poʻo le malamalama i se tasi poʻo se mea, pei o mea [[moni]] (faʻamatalaga malamalama), [[tomai]] (uō malamalama), poʻo mea [[faitino]] (masani iloa). I le tele o teuga tupe, malamalama mafai ona mauaina i le tele o auala 'eseʻese ma mai le tele o punaʻoa, aofia ai ae le gata i malamalamaaga, [[mafuaaga]], [[manatuaina]], [[molimau]], [[saienisi fesili]], [[aoaoga]], ma [[faiga]]. O le filosofia suesue o le poto e taua o le [[epistemology]]. 

O le upu "poto" e mafai ona faʻasino i se talitonuga se faʻale-mafaufa malamalamaaga pe faʻatinoina o se mataupu. E mafai ona faʻaalia (pei o le aoga o le agavaʻa poʻo se poto masani) poʻo le manino (pei o talitonuga malamalamaaga o se mataupu); aloaʻia pe faʻaletulafono; faʻavasega pe faʻapitoa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oxforddictionaries.com/view/entry/m_en_us1261368#m_en_us1261368 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100714023323/http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/view/entry/m_en_us1261368 |url-status=dead |archive-date=14 July 2010 |title=knowledge: definition of knowledge in Oxford dictionary (American English) (US) |work=oxforddictionaries.com }}</ref>

